The paper is about an interactive visualization tool for learning and experimenting with Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which are a popular class of complex deep learning models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since GANs are often used for image generation. The paper also involves aspects of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.GR (Graphics), as it deals with generative models and visualizations. Finally, the paper's focus on creating an accessible tool for non-experts suggests a potential fit with cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
